The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Delhi for Sindh

 New Delhi, March 23: The Centre has defended retaining the word ?Sindh? in the national anthem, stating before the Supreme Court that deleting the word would ?destroy? the anthem composed ?not in the geographical sense? of the country but in its unique ?cultural sense?, reports our legal correspondent.

 A PIL had said the word offended the sovereignty and territorial integrity of Pakistan. The Centre?s affidavit argued: ?The concern shown by the petitioner for... Pakistan is baseless and unpatriotic because in 1947-48 Pakistan forcibly occupied more than half of Kashmir.? 




